We are told of universal panic, in which even the highest stooped to the informer's trade, for self-preservation‚ or even as if infected by a plague; that men perished for old offences as much as for recent; for words as well as deeds3 even for words spoken in private life ⁶5 that even the walls seemed to have ears.

Here again the description seems somewhat to outstrip the facts.
